<HL>
   Michaels Stores' Sales Increase
</HL>
<DATE>
05/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   MKE
</CO>
<LP>
   IRVING, Texas -- Michaels Stores Inc. said April sales
rose 34% from a year earlier, with sales at stores open more
than a year rising about 18%.
   The crafts retailer said April sales rose to $27.2 million
from $20.3 million a year earlier. It attributed the showing
to the fact that Easter fell in April this year, whereas last
year it was in March.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first quarter ended April 29, Michaels said sales
increased about 28% to $71.7 million from $56.2 million.
Sales at stores open more than one year increased about 12%.
</TEXT>
